description:
&lt;p&gt;30 hours per week (part time, shifts) subject to further approval this vacancy may be offered at full time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Brampton and Longtown ICC have a vacancy for a band 6 Senior Physiotherapist (30 hours) to provide a range of adult community health services to people living within North Cumbria&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Its key ICC health focus is to provide care/assessments to prevent hospital admissions, facilitate early discharge and where possible to enable patients to manage their own conditions and remain in their own homes, thus enhancing both their independence and quality of life. We cover both the community and also Brampton community hospital (16 beds). This post flexes between the community hospital ward and community patients as caseload allows. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Within the community hospital ward you will be working as part of the MDT team comprising of OT, nursing staff, band 4/3 rehab assistants, GP’s and social workers. The aim of the ward is rehabilitation with swift and timely discharges back into the community or different settings as required. As a community Physiotherapist you will working largely alone and unsupervised to assess patients, plan and implement care in the community and a range of other settings, provide advice and education to patients, carers and colleagues, maintain associated records. The post holder will also be a source of expertise on a rota as lead professional of the day to triage referrals, prevent hospital admission and facilitate discharges. They will also assess patients for HCP support packages including any moving and handling requirements and work in close collaboration with our Adult social care colleagues to provide a seamless service for the patients. Within Brampton and Longtown ICC we have aspirations for a falls service, the post holder will also be actively encouraged to participate in this service development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will also carry out delegated management tasks including line management and clinical supervision of other team members and provide management cover in the absence of the Team Leader. The post holder will participate in the induction, training and education of students and other professionals including health, social services and voluntary organisations. They will also demonstrate a willingness to support service development, audit and research. The team and Trust are fully committed to support development, providing appropriate training, supervision and appraisals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post requires flexible working will be required to meet the needs of the patients group and will require 7 day working on a rota, including potentially some shift working to cover 8am – 6pm. The weekend working is located at hilltop heights to cover Brampton and Longtown ICC, Carlisle network and Carlisle Healthcare ICC.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There maybe an opportunity to rotate across the Acute setting depending on service demnds to be discussed at interview..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal discussion please call Rachel Webster – AHP team Lead 01946 853333 option 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Healthcare Professionals returning to practice, moving into new roles or changing clinical environments, may access an agreed preceptorship period.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please ensure that you document evidence of meeting all the essential criteria in the supporting information.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;If sufficient response is received this post could be closed earlier than the specified closing date, please apply as soon as possible to ensure that your application is considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust is committed to safeguarding adults and children therefore if the post is subject to the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (ROA) 1974 (Exceptions) Order 1975 (as amended) the successful candidate(s) will be subject to a criminal records check with the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS). The cost of the DBS must be met by the successful candidate(s) through salary deduction. DBS charges are as follows &lt;strong&gt;if applicable to the post:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Standard Check: £26 + Administration cost of £4.20 = deducted at £10.20 from 1st month salary and £10 deducted from salary over following 2 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Enhanced Check: £44 + administration cost of £4.20 = £15.20 deducted from 1st month salary and £11 deducted from salary over following 3 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of the one of the largest employers in the UK NCIC future employees will have also access to the following benefits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A lease car may be available for this position; further details will be provided upon appointment if applicable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;27 day holiday scheme rising to 33 after 10 years &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexible working Scheme &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent opportunities for development &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Competitive NHS Pension scheme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Access to NHS discounts with retailers and leisure companies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;EAP (Employee Assistance Programme) a free, confidential counselling and information service to assist with personal or work-related problems&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These schemes are subject to availability&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
